  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI have a test that fails when I set `user.timezone` to UTC I expect the config to have user.timezone to have UTC, this has worked for as long as this test is in, probably around quarkus 2.3, and now fails with quarkus 3.14\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntest should pass and config should return UTC\n\n### Actual behavior\n\ndoes not return UTC\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nReproducer: https://github.com/manofthepeace/quarkus-test-overrides\r\n\r\nStep to reproduce;\r\n1- run the test, it will fail\r\n2- change the quarkus version in the pom to 3.13.3\r\n3- rerun the test, it will pass.\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nDarwin Kernel Version 21.6.0\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nopenjdk version \"21.0.4\" 2024-07-16 LTS\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n3.14.1\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nmvn 3.9.9\n\n### Additional information\n\nin the pom file added the following on top the the provided one by the code start;\r\n`<jvm.args>-Duser.timezone=UTC</jvm.args>`",
